[The state of Kentucky can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5345702,8660. Pulaski county in southern Kentucky can be seen on the map at http://geology.com/county-map/kentucky-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ

Regardless of location, mosquitoes can and do carry diseases. It is imperative we protect our animals and ourselves. The West Nile virus vaccination for horses is usually combined with eastern equine encephalitis, western equine encephalitis, and tetanus vaccines. This one injection needs to be given twice, about 3-4 weeks apart. There are specific mosquito repellent sprays for horses. Please also remember to wear your own mosquito repellent. The disease in humans is not pleasant, I understand. - Mod.TG]
